	   <a name=101681111089064></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101681111089064><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Impatience leads to annoyance...sorry</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Sage>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>147 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 22nd 10:34 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think a number of people have answerd most of your questions, so I will only address one:&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;Why aren't Shaman asked for more often?&quot;  <br>You are right we do have some great spells, Haste, slow, Dots, SoW, Regen etc.  Regretfully we are not the only classes with these abilities.  For a group our Slow and Haste are the most important.  Chanters and Bards can also slow and haste.  What's more they can increasse mana regain rate, and they can mez mobs.  Do to these other abilities these classes are always chossen before the shaman.  It is really too bad that we are the thrid choice to do what we do best.  As far as buffs, at upper lvl the most asked for buffs are Str and dex.  The shaman has the better Str buff but can't beat boon for dex and boon give life tap as well.  <br>The only thing worth wile Shaman can do that these classes can't is cast sow. but here again we are only thrid best when compaired to Druids and Rangers.  Durids have many more and better group buffs and they can evac and TP the group around, not to menction track.  Rangers give added melee power and can track as well.  <br><br>In short the efforts of Verant to make Chanters, Druids, and Rangers more groupable over the years has pushed the Shaman to the side line. I have been in one group with a shaman this year.  (I also play a war lvl 52) I think it has been over 6 month since I have be in a full group with my Lvl 51 shaman.  <br>However I do solo with my shaman or team up with one or two others from time to time.  I will also log my shaman on to buff a raid party, and then attend the raid as my warrior.<br>For a full group the shaman just can't compete with the chanters, bards and durids, however we do solo well and are good in groups of 2 or 3. The down side of this is EQ is moving more and more to group and two or 3 groups needed to make the kills that result in good loot.  <br>Will Varent save the Shaman during the spell caster rebalanceing?  To my knowlage every time changes have been made that impacted the shaman class the shaman has gotten weaker.....  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
